# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Allow new devices for staff connected at a MoJ site via physcial network cable to retrieve a internet address and [MoJ DNS](dns.html) servers.

## User needs

This allows Public internet connectivity for prison staff to enable modern devices

## Principles

Provide a self service portal for onsite administrators to add e.g. a static reservation for a printer


## Tools

The backend DHCP service will use the well established and open source version called ISC Kea running as containers in the AWS managed container service Fargate.